{{original research|date=August 2017}}<!-- The way three of the cited sources use the term, it applies *only* to West Bengal, not to any portion of Bangladesh. It isn't clear whether the north-south divisions are common, or are ad-hoc for the particular sources (Panwar, for example, writes "for the sake of convenience the state [of West Bengal] has been divided into two parts: north Bengal and south Bengal"). Moreover, the sources don't agree about which districts are in the north and which are in the south. According to Christiana, for example, Murshidabad is in North Bengal, not South. --> [[File:South Bengal in Bengal.png|thumb|South Bengal is marked red in Bengal Region]]
'''South Bengal''' ({{lang-bn|দক্ষিণ বঙ্গ}}/ দক্ষিণ বাংলা) is a term used for the southern parts of [[Bengal]] including Southern [[Bangladesh]] and Southern West Bengal.
The Bangladesh part denotes the [[Khulna Division]], [[Barisal Division]] and proposed [[Faridpur Division]]. [[Bay of Bengal]] is located at the end of southern part of Bangladesh.<ref name="Deen">{{cite book|last=Deen|first=Prof. S. M.|title=A Brief History of Bengal for Diaspora Bangladeshis|url=https://books.google.de/books/about/A_Brief_History_of_Bengal_for_Diaspora_B.html?id=RpNaCAAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y|year=2014|publisher=[[Lulu Press]], Inc|isbn=9781326023775|page=59}} {{self-published inline|date=August 2017}}</ref><ref>https://books.google.de/books?id=PpIzAFZ5zZEC&pg=PA16&dq=South+Bengal+area+districts&hl=de&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiZwJG_puXVAhXEPFAKHaWwBGQQ6AEINjAC#v=onepage&q=South%20Bengal%20area%20districts&f=false</ref>
