'''The Minaret''' ({{coord|64|46|S|63|39|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a steep [[rock pinnacle]], {{Convert|1,065|m|-2}} high, on the ridge extending northeast from [[Mount William (Antarctica)|Mount William]] in the southern part of [[Anvers Island]], in the [[Palmer Archipelago]], Antarctica. It was surveyed by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] in 1944 and again in 1955. The name, given by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]], is descriptive of the shape of the summit, suggesting a [[minaret]].<ref name=gnis/>

